Build a production-grade fintech web application called "STACKR" — an intelligent credit card recommendation and comparison platform for Indian users.

The product must not be a UI demo. It must function as a real-world, data-driven, personalized decision engine with backend infrastructure, APIs, user accounts, and monetization via affiliate integrations.

---

## 🎯 CORE OBJECTIVE

Help users discover the best credit cards based on:

* Their actual spending behavior
* Financial profile (income, credit score)
* Preferences (travel, cashback, fuel, insurance)

The system must:

1. Calculate real yearly value (₹) for each card
2. Rank cards dynamically using weighted + computed logic
3. Provide explainable recommendations
4. Enable comparison and application

---

## 🧱 TECH STACK (STRICT)

Frontend:

* React (Next.js preferred)
* TailwindCSS (minimal, clean, professional — NOT flashy)
* Framer Motion (subtle animations)

Backend:

* Node.js + Express OR NestJS
* REST API (GraphQL optional)

Database:

* PostgreSQL (structured financial data)
* Redis (caching frequently accessed card rankings)

Auth:

* Firebase Auth OR JWT-based auth

Hosting:

* Vercel (frontend)
* AWS / Render / Railway (backend)

---

## 📊 DATABASE DESIGN (CRITICAL — POINT 13)

Design normalized tables:

1. users

* id
* name
* email
* password_hash
* monthly_income
* credit_score
* spending_profile (JSON: categories with ₹ values)
* created_at

2. cards

* id
* name
* bank
* type (cashback, travel, fuel, rewards)
* joining_fee
* annual_fee
* reward_rate
* cashback_rules (JSON)
* lounge_access
* fuel_benefits
* insurance_details
* eligibility_score_min
* affiliate_link
* last_updated

3. offers

* id
* card_id
* title
* description
* expiry_date
* bonus_value

4. user_activity

* id
* user_id
* action (viewed, compared, applied)
* card_id
* timestamp

5. applications (for tracking monetization)

* id
* user_id
* card_id
* status (clicked, redirected, approved)
* affiliate_source
* timestamp

---

## 🌐 DATA INTEGRATION (POINT 13 - ADVANCED)

Implement real-world data ingestion:

1. APIs / Scraping:

* Bank websites (HDFC, SBI, Axis, ICICI)
* Financial aggregators (Paisabazaar, BankBazaar)
* RBI / public financial data

2. Build a cron job system:

* Refresh card data every 24 hours
* Validate:

  * Fees
  * Rewards
  * Offers

3. Data normalization layer:

* Convert all reward formats into unified structure:
  Example:

  * cashback_percentage
  * reward_points_value (₹ equivalent)

4. Fallback system:

* If API fails → use last cached data (Redis)

---

## 🧠 RECOMMENDATION ENGINE (CORE LOGIC)

Inputs:

* Monthly spend per category:

  * shopping
  * travel
  * fuel
  * bills
* Income
* Credit score
* Preferences (slider weights)

Processing:

1. Calculate yearly spend

2. Apply card-specific reward rules

3. Compute:

   * Total cashback (₹)
   * Total fees
   * Net benefit = cashback - fees

4. Generate score:
   score = weighted(normalized benefits + perks + eligibility match)

5. Output:

* Top ranked cards
* Exact ₹ benefit/year

---

## 📈 CASHBACK CALCULATOR (REAL)

User inputs spending → system outputs:

* Cashback per card
* Monthly + yearly breakdown

Add:

* Graph visualization (bar chart)
* “Best card saves you ₹X more than #2”

